-- Nissan’s Misaki Says China’s Auto Sales Growth Is Sustainable
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2011-12-16T05:05:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-16/nissan-s-misaki-says-china-s-auto-sales-growth-is-sustainable.html
Masami Misaki,  Nissan Motor Co. (7201) ’s
vice president for  China  operations, comments on prospects for
auto sales in the country in 2012. He spoke in an interview in
Beijing today.  On China’s auto demand in 2012:  The increase in auto sales in China “will continue for
sustainable growth. Growth next year will be a bit higher than
this year.”  China’s overall auto sales gain in 2012 “may be beyond 10
percent” if demand for commercial vehicles increases.  On Nissan’s growth in China next year:  “We would like to continue this year’s growth in China.”  --Tian Ying. Editor: Lena Lee, Subramaniam Sharma  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
Tian Ying in Beijing at 
